.alert.alert-info.mb-4.d-block
  %p
    %strong Each row connects the warehouse to an external identity provider (IDP).
    A config is
    %strong not
    required for sign-in. Adding a config lets the warehouse manage user accounts (where supported) and show a friendly IDP name.
  %p
    %strong Connector ID
    is the routing key the auth proxy sends with each login. It must exactly match the value the proxy is configured with, or users from that IDP won't be matched to a config.
